place_description: Gulmarg, known as Gulmarag in Kashmiri, is a town, hill station, tourist destination, skiing destination, and a notified area committee in the Baramulla district in the Indian union territory of Jammu and Kashmir. It is located at a distance of 31 km from Baramulla and 49 km from Srinagar. Wikipedia.

top_attractions.detail_description: Gulmarg, a stunning destination in Kashmir, is situated in the Pir Panjal range of the Western Himalayas. Perched at an elevation of 8,690 feet above sea level, this charming town is surrounded by glistening snow-capped mountains, lush green meadows, vibrant floral fields, deep valleys, and pine-clad slopes. It is renowned for its ski resort that was established back in 1927.
top_attractions.name: Gulmarg Ski Resort
top_attractions.address: The Khyber, On Gondola Road, road, near Govt. Hospital, Gulmarg, Jammu and Kashmir 193403

top_attractions.detail_description: Afarwat, located in Gulmarg, India, is a popular mountain peak among skiers and adventure travelers. The area offers dense pine trees and stunning views of Mount Afarwat. The Khyber Himalayan Resort & Spa is conveniently situated near the Gulmarg gondolas and features signposted trails leading back to the property from the mountaintop.
top_attractions.excerpt: Tall mountain peak popular with skiers & adventure travelers with a gondola ski lift for visitors.
top_attractions.name: Afarwat

top_attractions.detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Baramulla, Khilanmarg Woods is a breathtaking destination that enchants both locals and travelers alike. Known for its vibrant meadows adorned with colorful flowers, this picturesque spot offers stunning panoramic views of the majestic Himalayan mountain ranges and lush valleys of Kashmir. Often referred to as the Meadow of Flowers, Khilanmarg is a visual delight where nature's beauty unfolds against a backdrop of snow-capped peaks.
top_attractions.name: Khilanmarg Woods

top_attractions.detail_description: Gulmarg's Golf Course offers a stunning expanse of lush greenery nestled amidst majestic mountains and peaks. Situated at an impressive altitude of 2,600 meters, it stands as one of the highest golf courses globally. This historic course has been a venue for numerous prestigious golf championships and traces its origins back to the British colonial era.
top_attractions.name: Golf course

top_attractions.detail_description: Gulmarg Golf Course offers a fantastic natural setting, surrounded by breathtaking views and a serene atmosphere.
top_attractions.name: Gulmarg Golf Course

top_attractions.detail_description: Nestled in the enchanting landscape of Gulmarg, St. Mary’s Church is a captivating 19th-century Anglican church that beautifully reflects the region's colonial history. Constructed in 1902, this charming structure showcases stunning Victorian architecture and offers a serene atmosphere for visitors seeking tranquility away from the lively tourist areas. Surrounded by breathtaking natural beauty, including lush valleys and snow-capped peaks, St. Mary’s Church serves as an ideal spot for quiet reflection or spiritual solace.
top_attractions.name: St. Mary’s Church, Gulmarg

The area is popular for skiing, snowboarding, snow scooters, and snow bobbing. The staff are professional, passionate about skiing, and provide guidance throughout the journey. They offer seamless booking processes and organize entire trips including transportation, accommodation, equipment rental, experienced guides and instructors.

top_attractions.detail_description: The Gulmarg Gondola is a must-visit attraction, offering an exhilarating cable car ride that takes you to an altitude of 14,000 feet above sea level. As the second highest and second longest cable car in the world, it provides breathtaking views of Gulmarg and Khilanmarg, allowing visitors to marvel at the natural beauty of the Himalayas.

top_attractions.detail_description: Kongdori is a breathtaking destination divided into two sections, with a gondola ride that takes you to Apherwat. The journey offers stunning views of pine forests and mesmerizing landscapes. Visitors have described it as 'heaven on earth' and 'a place to see nature's beauty up close.' Some recommend purchasing gondola tickets in advance due to long wait times, while others advise against it for seniors or those with mobility issues.

top_attractions.detail_description: Buta Pathri, situated in the charming hill station of Gulmarg in Jammu and Kashmir, India, is a stunning meadow offering breathtaking views of snow-capped mountains. At an altitude of around 11,000 feet, this picturesque location provides visitors with a serene and tranquil atmosphere. Travelers can enjoy the beauty of Buta Pathri while taking a horse ride up the hill or by booking a taxi to explore the scenic surroundings.
top_attractions.name: Buta Pathri
